  "description": "<i>Solitaire</i> is a 1-player card game for the 8-bit Atari.<br><br>Simulates the 7-column card game Solitaire using a single deck.  Uses typical casino rules, where the player draws 1 card at a time, but can only go through the deck a single time.  The player is rewarded $5 for each card played on an ace.  The player can choose to repeat the deck again, but does not receive further winnings.  Each game is timed.",
